The course objective is to identify main natural resources, their spatial distribution, describe assessment methods and to introduce the way for sustainable use of natural resources. As a result of the course students will prepare an essay and will give an presentation during the seminars.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to identify main natural resources, their spatial distribution and to introduce the way for their sustainable use.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student understands character of natural resources, methods to classify and estimate reserves. Is able to understand spatial distribution and use of natural resources and related problems. Has a solid knowledge of terminology, scientific background and relation to other scientific diciplines.
